
Amazon Route 53 is a scalable and highly available Domain Name System (DNS) web service provided by AWS. 

Route 53 simplifies managing DNS records and routing traffic to your web applications.

Key Features of Route 53:

DNS Management: You can create and manage DNS records for your domain names.
Domain Registration: You can register new domain names directly through Route 53.
Health Checks: Route 53 can monitor the health of your application and route traffic away from unhealthy resources.
Traffic Management: Route 53 offers various routing policies like simple, weighted, latency-based, and geo-location routing.


types of records:
1. www.example.com. 300 IN A 192.0.2.1
2. www.example.com. 300 IN AAAA 2001:0db8:85a3:0000:0000:8a2e:0370:7334
3. blog.example.com. 300 IN CNAME www.example.com.
4. example.com. 300 IN MX 10 mail.example.com.

